#: ../../user/troubleshooting/gui-troubleshooting.rst:3
#: d1c39f339e14474bba2aee0e75c3bd71
msgid "GUI troubleshooting"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/gui-troubleshooting.rst:7
#: 83a335dd495243b5a519fe8ac4b3c94f
msgid ""
"Can't click on parts of the screen after connecting high-resolution "
"external display"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/gui-troubleshooting.rst:10
#: 3647d345ae39429187c4fb5fe83cfde9
msgid ""
"When you connect a high-resolution external display, you may be unable to"
" click on parts of the screen."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/gui-troubleshooting.rst:12
#: 9fe80e22b342403297366b319325ee3a
msgid ""
"When a qube starts, a fixed amount of RAM is allocated to the graphics "
"buffer called video RAM. This buffer needs to be at least as big as the "
"whole desktop, accounting for all displays that are or will be connected "
"to the machine. By default, it is as much as needed for the current "
"display and an additional full HD (FHD) display (1920×1080 8 bit/channel "
"RGBA). This logic fails when the machine has primary display in FHD "
"resolution and, after starting some qubes, a high-resolution display is "
"connected. If the buffer is too small, and internal desktop resize fails."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/gui-troubleshooting.rst:14
#: 39c7e40289854abba51fbe145f6fec5e
msgid ""
"To determine if this is the problem affecting you, look at the Xorg log "
"inside the Qube at ``/home/user/.local/share/xorg/Xorg.0.log`` for lines "
"like the following:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/gui-troubleshooting.rst:22
#: 80e42c5692dc4b4a803c5bc39fbb224f
msgid ""
"The solution to this problem is to increase the minimum size of the video"
" RAM buffer, as explained in :ref:`GUI Configuration <user/advanced-"
"topics/gui-configuration:video ram adjustment for high-resolution "
"displays>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/gui-troubleshooting.rst:25
#: 851ae93c60c64ce8ab254b39c1e44a98
msgid ""
"Screen blanks / Weird computer glitches like turning partially black or "
"black boxes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/gui-troubleshooting.rst:28
#: 43525c2b7da04cdbb39d4a7782603a77
msgid ""
"You may encountering seemingly random screen blanking while using Qubes, "
"where the screen will black and shows the logon screen, yet, only the "
"active window will show when you move the mouse or use the keyboard. "
"Sometimes, you will get random black screens or black boxes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/gui-troubleshooting.rst:30
#: da7cc0017c334553b305d487f6f0c15b
msgid ""
"Similarly, while working, the XScreenSaver dialog may pop up (indicating "
"the screen is locked) and the screen goes black. However, the screen is "
"not locked, and you have to move a window to redraw the screen."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/gui-troubleshooting.rst:32
#: 9d9f0f60a4454865bc7c70575f716968
msgid ""
"If you are experiencing the any of the above symptoms, try disabling the "
"window compositor:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/gui-troubleshooting.rst:34
#: 06d206d78c614297a592214c87f2afd8
msgid ""
"``Q → System Tools → Window Manager Tweaks → Compositor → uncheck “Enable"
" display compositing”``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/gui-troubleshooting.rst:37
#: ddcde8d543b04cbea4c0dc645e3ea670
msgid "Post installation, screen goes black and freezes following LUKS decryption"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/gui-troubleshooting.rst:40
#: 7c776dd8c1a4427d95b8238dd5adf77e
msgid ""
"After installing Qubes, you may experience a black screen after entering "
"your LUKS decryption password. To fix the problem, use your preferred "
"text editor (``nano`` works) to edit "
"``/mnt/sysimage/boot/efi/EFI/qubes/xen.cfg``, adding the ``efi=no-rs`` "
"option to the end of the ``options= line``. For example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/gui-troubleshooting.rst:49
#: 4cd760133af44bdfa26c9bcc694adb9b
msgid ""
"Note that the ``/mnt/sysimage/boot/efi/EFI/qubes/xen.cfg`` path applies "
"when running from the installer (either directly after installation, "
"before the reboot, or by starting the installer again in recovery mode). "
"On the actual installed system, the file to edit is "
"``/boot/efi/EFI/qubes/xen.cfg`` – but it may be hard to access directly "
"when your system won’t boot."
msgstr ""

